The paper introduces a new approach to learning approximate Nash equilibria in large-scale games of imperfect information using deep reinforcement learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with game theory and optimization, which are covered by the sub-categories of Game Theory (cs.GT) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper applies the proposed method to a real-world game, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
